Configuring Storybook can be scary sometimes.

Here's how to set up a @nextjs app with @tailwindcss and @storybookjs in a short thread.

This is the game plan:

1. Bootstrap Next.js with create-next-app
2. Set up Tailwindcss
3. Configure Storybook

Before we move on, let's remove the CSS Module stuff to get ready for Tailwind:

1/ remove the CSS Module file at `styles/Home.module.css`
2/ replace the home page content with a good ol' Hello World

Much better! We're now ready to move on to TailwindCSS! https://t.co/0lPDWcxW1J

2. Set up Tailwindcss in a few steps:

1/ install dependencies

$ yarn add -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer

2/ init Tailwind

$ npx tailwindcss init -p

3/ configure `tailwind.config.js` to watch relevant files

4/ replace `styles/globals.css` content with TailwindCSS import https://t.co/g9icJXL5UG
